FILE 9: /home/vasu-hdd/yocto-gateway-rt/layers/meta-cclrte/recipes-realtime/rt-setup/files/rt-setup.sh

Complete bash script (set -euo pipefail) that:

1. Log function: log() { echo "[$(date -Iseconds)] CCLRTE-RT: $*" | tee -a /var/log/cclrte-rt.log; }

2. Set IRQ affinity: all IRQs to CPU0,1 (smp_affinity_list = 0-1 for each /proc/irq/*/smp_affinity_list)

3. Find EtherCAT NIC IRQ (search for the NIC used for EtherCAT - eth0 by default, get its IRQ from /proc/interrupts) and set its smp_affinity_list to CPU2

4. Set EtherCAT process to SCHED_FIFO priority 90 when it exists (use chrt -f -p 90 <pid>). Loop via pgrep ec_master or ethercat-related process.

5. Set CODESYS process to SCHED_FIFO priority 80 when it exists (pgrep codesyscontrol or codesysruntime)

6. Set CODESYS process memory lock: use prlimit to set RLIMIT_MEMLOCK=unlimited for codesys PID

7. Set kernel.sched_rt_runtime_us=-1 via sysctl (already in sysctl.conf but do it here too as belt-and-suspenders)

8. Log completion and latency hint: suggest running rt-verify

Include a function wait_for_process() that waits up to 30s for a process to appear.

